value.title: Trump returns to campaign trail with Minnesota rally after widely panned debate
value.excerpt: Trump and his campaign see Minnesota as a special project, their best chance to flip a state Hillary Clinton won in 2016. Biden is leading in polls.

value.title: Federal judge refuses to stop mail-in voting in Montana, blasts Trump-backed 'fiction' of massive voter fraud
value.excerpt: A federal judge in Montana rejected the Trump campaign's effort to stop an expansion of mail-in voting in the state.

value.title: Wisconsin gov tells Trump to require masks at state rallies — or skip them
value.excerpt: Gov. Tony Evers suggested President Trump not come to Wisconsin for two campaign rallies this weekend, as the state struggles with record-breaking numbers of hospitalizations and new coronavirus cases.

value.title: Trump says he doesn't know who Proud Boys are, says 'let law enforcement do their work'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday tried to clear up confusion after telling the right-wing men’s group the Proud Boys to “stand back and stand by,” saying he didn’t know who the group was but they should let law enforcement do their job.

value.title: Chicago Mayor Lightfoot slams Trump after he blasts Windy City violence
value.excerpt: Democratic Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot fired back at President Trump on Tuesday night after he skewered her city during a presidential campaign debate against Joe Biden as a hotbed of crime and violence.

value.title: Biden says at debate he doesn't support Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it 'crucial framework'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden said Tuesday night at the first presidential debate that he does not support the Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it a “crucial framework” for meeting climate change challenges.

value.title: Former Playboy Playmate Karen McDougal says she’s ‘been forgiven by Jesus’ for alleged Trump affair
value.excerpt: During the 2016 election, National Enquirer parent company American Media Inc. paid McDougal $150,000 for the rights to her story, which it never published. The company eventually acknowledged the purchase was a “catch-and-kill” maneuver to boost Trump's presidential prospects.

value.title: Joe Biden and Kamala Harris don't want to talk about changes to the Supreme Court
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Kamala Harris made it clear on Tuesday night that they don't want to talk about changes to the Supreme Court, including expanding the current nine-justice bench.

value.title: Why did Trump's Intel chief launch a dubious pre-debate gambit?
value.excerpt: The disclosure from DNI was quickly overshadowed by last night's debate, but even by 2020 standards, this was extraordinary.

value.title: Comey says new information that Hillary Clinton drummed up Russia controversy to vilify Trump 'doesn’t ring a bell'
value.excerpt: Former FBI Director James Comey on Wednesday said it didn’t “ring a bell” when asked whether he received an investigative referral on Hillary Clinton purportedly approving “a plan” attempting to tie President Trump to Russia and distract from her email scandal before the 2016 election.

value.title: Florida's top city for Cuban exiles goes to bat for GOP in 2020: 'Trump Town'
value.excerpt: The city of Hialeah, outside Miami, is known for its Cuban American community of working families, tight incomes and friendships among neighbors -- and as the election nears, many say they're leaning strongly toward voting for President Trump.

value.title: The Point: Donald Trump has a long history of refusing to condemn white supremacist and hate groups
value.excerpt: Asked directly during Tuesday night's debate to condemn the Proud Boys hate group, President Donald Trump told them to "stand back and stand by."

value.title: CNN’s Don Lemon suggests Trump was ‘hopped up’ on performance-enhancing drugs during debate
value.excerpt: CNN’s Don Lemon suggested that President Trump appeared to be “hopped up” on a performance-enhancing drug during Tuesday night’s presidential debate.

value.title: Could California’s policies work on a federal scale under a Biden-Harris administration?
value.excerpt: California has long been known for its push toward more progressive policies, many of which now form the basis of the Joe Biden-Kamala Harris presidential ticket. But whether or not such proposals have been successful – and whether California should be lauded as a model, is subject to debate.

value.title: Donald Trump sidesteps call to condemn white supremacists — and the Proud Boys were 'extremely excited' about it
value.excerpt: Debate moderator Chris Wallace asked if Donald Trump would urge groups to stand down and avoid contributing to the violence. He sidestepped.

value.title: Trump said Portland's sheriff supports him. The sheriff disputes that.
value.excerpt: "In tonight's presidential debate the President said the 'Portland Sheriff' supports him. As the Multnomah County Sheriff I have never supported Donald Trump and will never support him," Sheriff Mike Reese tweeted.

value.title: SNL is back this weekend with Jim Carrey as Joe Biden, Chris Rock as host and a whole lot of restrictions. Here’s what to expect.
value.excerpt: Live" will return for its 46th season with more Alec Baldwin as Trump, Maya Rudolph as Kamala Harris and three new cast members.

value.title: Matt Gorman: Trump has a new running mate now
value.excerpt: Yes, Vice President Mike Pence is still around. And no, the near-constant chatter about former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley did not come to pass.

value.title: Sheriff in Portland denies Trump's debate claim of winning his endorsement
value.excerpt: The sheriff of Multnomah County, which includes Portland, Ore., emphatically denied supporting President Trump Tuesday evening shortly after the president made the claim.

value.title: Biden: 'He's the racist'
value.excerpt: During the first presidential debate, President Donald Trump claimed he ended racial sensitivity training because it was "racist" and Joe Biden responded that Trump is the racist.

value.title: Ross asked if ending census earlier would produce numbers in Trump's current term
value.excerpt: Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross' surprise decision Monday evening to end 2020 census counting on October 5 risks an incomplete tally of as many as 10 states, including Florida and Georgia, according to Census Bureau officials.
